cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.MM

This paper focuses on improving the throughput of cellular networks through the use of Device-to-Device (D2D) communications and caching. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses frequency band allocation and optimization, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of clustering and spatial reuse gain suggests a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The management of interference among D2D links could also be relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the caching aspect of the paper could potentially fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
